  "body": "### User Story\nAs a user, I want to update the desktop app using a \"Check for updates\" option on the [MacOS app menu](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/5547), so I can update my app easily. \n\n### Description\n*Type*: Feature\n\n*Summary*: \nEnable a \"Check for updates\" option in MacOS menu bar. Allow the update and automatic installation of new version.\n\n#### Expected behavior / Solution\nThe user flow would be:\n- The user has Status desktop open\n- She selects the new option \"Check for updates\" on the menu bar #5547 \n- A new window shows the new update notes. E.g.\n<img width=\"639\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-09-12 a la s 2 11 18 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/45424109-c4075f80-b695-11e8-920b-652240ef09c8.png\">\n- She selects \"Install update\"\n- Update gets extracted (maybe we don't need this step?). Eg.\n<img width=\"419\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-09-12 a la s 2 12 09 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/45424157-eb5e2c80-b695-11e8-8316-c1f45597ace6.png\">\n- The user is asked to Install and Relaunch the app\n<img width=\"442\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-09-12 a la s 2 12 13 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/45424175-f1540d80-b695-11e8-8cd8-2003e6376f49.png\">\n- After doing so, the new version of the app opens again, already logged in and in the latest chat/section/position of the app.\n\n#### Actual behavior\nThere is a random button on the profile screen to upgrade:\n\n<img width=\"342\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-10-24 a la s 1 00 32 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/47426283-12c41100-d78d-11e8-9f3d-604dd0677fc1.png\">\n\nThis presents the following problems:\n- Compites on hierarchy with \"Share contact code\"\n- Doesn't leave space for more options under profile. If more options are added, it will get lost.\n- Not an standard place to check for updates among MacOS apps.\n\n### Additional Information\nTBD how to do this on Linux and Windows\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://status-im.github.io/nightly/\">Status.im Nightly Builds</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
